==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liability
<hw>Li`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧`⟦adot⟧*b⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Liabilities</plw>
<pr>(-t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being liable; <as>as, the
<ex>liability</ex> of an insurer; <ex>liability</ex> to accidents;
<ex>liability</ex> to the law.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which one is under obligation to pay, or for
which one is liable.</def> Specifically, in the <pluf>pl.</pluf>,
<def>the sum of one's pecuniary obligations; -- opposed to
<contr>assets</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Limited liability</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Limited
company</cref>, under <er>Limited</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liable</ent>⟦br⟧
